o bail in the sum of  N200,000 with two sureties in like sum. He ordered that the sureties must be gainfully employed and have evidence of three years’ tax payment to the Lagos State Government. Nwaka adjourned the case until Jan. 9, 2020, for mention. Vanguard News Nigeria. A 24-year-old applicant, Ade Adeniyi, who allegedly stole a purse containing N20,000, was on Wednesday, arraigned in an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court. January 24, 2018 In "News" A 19-year-old painter, Oladipupo Ibukun , who allegedly stole N18, 000 and a cell phone valued at N19, 000, was on Wednesday arraigned in an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court. November 1, 2017 In "News" Lagos—A 56-year-old estate agent, Segun Alade, was Tuesday, arraigned before a Lagos Magistrate Court, sitting in Ikeja, for allegedly obtaining N600,000 from one Adesanya Adegbesan, under the pretence of getting him an accommodation. June 19, 2013 In "News"